[4] India (Gujarat)
Date: Mon 13 Feb 2018 04:00 IST
Source: The Times of India, Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/rajkot/nri-man-dies-of-swine-flu-in-patan/articleshow/62890257.cms


A 52-year-old NRI (non-resident Indian) from Saudi Arabia [MCS] died of swine flu [influenza A/H1N1] in Dharpur Medical College of Patan [Gujarat] on [Mon 12 Feb 2018]. His wife [SS], who was suspected to be infected with [influenza A/H1N1] virus, died at a private hospital in Patan last [Fri 2 Feb 2018].

The couple had come to their native in Patan about 3 months ago along with their son and were residing at Kali Bazaar in Patan. The couple was to return to Saudi Arabia later this month [February 2018].

"While [M] tested positive for H1N1 virus on [Mon 12 Feb 2018] before his death, his wife died of suspected swine flu at a private hospital last [Fri 2 Feb 2018]," chief district health officer (CDHO) of Patan Bharat Goswami said. "Son of the deceased couple is also suffering from the cough and cold and is under treatment. A medical team is reviewing the 1st swine flu case of the season," Goswami added.

Goswami further said, "We are taking all possible preventive measures on a war-footing. 3 survey teams are now conducting the surveillance work in the affected area and medicines are being provided to affected people. We have so far surveyed about 158 houses and found 12 cases of cold and cough."

